post_text: Dear Synergy Families, We are excited to begin the 20-21 school year with our Distance Learning program. The first day of Distance Learning for all students is Wednesday, August 5th. For the health and safety of our families, this year's Meet the Teacher will be a 2-Day, Drive-Through event. See below the details of the event and look for a letter coming this week with the name of your child's teacher. In addition, class lists will be posted outside of the front office on Wednesday, July 29th. During the Drive-Through event, please ensure that everyone in your car is wearing a face mask.

post_text:
ALL STUDENTS WILL BEGIN THE UPCOMING SCHOOL YEAR ON-LINE, AUGUST 5th.

All Synergy students will begin distance learning on Wednesday, August 5th. Then students whose parents have chosen On-Campus learning will transition to physical classrooms when it is safe to return. Parents who would like to continue On-Line learning will have that option as we continue through the school year.

We are excited to begin the school year where students will engage in live lessons and recorded lessons with teachers daily. It is important that we start on August 5th and begin learning as soon as possible.

post_text:
Good Evening Synergy families,

Today Governor Ducey held a Press Conference and has delayed the start of school until Aug. 17, 2020 due to COVID-19's rising numbers in the State of Arizona. At this time we are working out the schedules and details of when the 20-21 school year will begin. We know that you all have a lot of questions, as do we. We are working hard to get the answers and as soon as we know anything we will let you know.

You will receive updated information through our website, Facebook page, phone calls and mailings.

We hope that we will see you very soon!!!

post_text:
Good evening Synergy families, We want to provide you the most up-to-date information on the status of Arizona’s school closures. Over the last week, the state has been working side-by-side to keep parents and educators informed with the latest developments.

On Friday, March 20th the state added an extension to the school closures through April 10, 2020. Beginning tomorrow, Monday, March 23rd breakfast and lunch meals will be provided to anyone who is 18 years of age or under. Meals will be distributed in front of the school office as a drive through service beginning at 9:00am – 11:00am. You will receive both breakfast and lunch at that time.

On Tuesday, March 24, 2020 student work will be distributed to families when picking up meals or during the office hours of 9:00am – 2:00pm.

We hope that you are all safe and healthy. We are looking forward to opening our doors for our students once the state and federal restrictions are lifted.

Good Evening Synergy Families,

As of 4:00 PM on Sunday, March 15, 2020, Governor Doug Ducey and State Superintendent Kathy Hoffman jointly announced the closure of all Arizona schools from Monday, March 16, 2020 through Friday, March 27, 2020.

We will continue to keep all of our families abreast of this situation through phone calls, Synergy’s webpage and social media as we continue to learn more information.

post_text: Synergy Families, We have many questions regarding the closing of Synergy Public School due to the COVID-19 virus. Please know that the health and safety of our students, staff and community are our first priority. Since we are already on Spring Break next week, March 16th through the 20th, we will be monitoring the COVID-19 virus closely during that time and make a decision by the middle of next week, if we will be closed the week of March 23rd. If a closure is necessary, we will inform parents through a school-wide phone call as well as social media and our website. Today we will be sending a parent letter home with your students. Feel free to reach out if you have any additional questions. We hope you all enjoy your Spring Break next week.

post_text: On behalf of Synergy Public School we would like to send out our deepest condolences on the recent passing of our beloved friend and colleague Adrian Castro. Synergy and the entire school community has lost a very special person who had a gentle soul and a kind heart. Adrian was generous, loving and dedicated to his work, children and family. May our hearts soon be filled with wonderful memories of joyful times together as we celebrate a life well lived. Adrian will be sorely missed.

post_text: If you don't believe in the magic of Christmas, let us show you through the eyes of a child. Magic filled the Synergy Courtyard this morning with a visit from Santa, a reading of The Polar Express, Sing-A-Long and of course the presents! Every child at Synergy received a Synergy sweatshirt, gloves, candy and a stuffed animal thanks to the support of many business partners. Petsmart Store 1145, Genesis Metal Corp., Metal of Honor, Hobaica Services, Perusek Inc. DBA Triangle Sheetmetal, EZ Innovations, Hercules Industries and multiple private donations from family and friends. We could not have made this happen without your generous support. Happy Holidays from Synergy Public School.

Ms. Smith's Art Studio has been busy visiting Egypt this week. Kindergarteners used their knowledge of shapes to make Egyptian Pharaoh and Queen Collars.

post_text:
Dear Synergy Families, In lieu of the teacher walk-outs in the state of Arizona, we want to let you know that Synergy Public School will remain open, with business as usual.

As a school, we support our teachers and staff as they work to gain the attention of our state legislators relating to the under funding of public schools. During this process, we aim to ensure that our daily commitment to providing a high quality, safe learning environment for our students and staff is not compromised.

We are continuously impressed with the commitment and dedication that our staff demonstrates to our students. We appreciate their devotion and heartfelt passion that they give to your children each and every day. Our high caliber of teachers and staff is what makes Synergy Public School exceptional. #Redfored
